#week-title("Three", "Recognising the Secret Fire")

=== Core Teaching

The "Secret Fire" referred to in the alchemical literature is not merely a
poetic name for heat. It is a specific phenomenon: the vital force present
within the mineral itself, operating autonomously once the correct conditions
have been established by the practitioner.

*How to recognise it.* The Secret Fire manifests in a preparation as:

- *Autonomous colour change* — colour transitions occurring in a sealed vessel
  without any external intervention; changes that could not be explained by
  simple oxidation or reduction alone.
- *Self-generated warmth* — in some preparations at an advanced stage, the
  flask is perceptibly warmer than its surroundings, even in the absence of
  external heating. This is rare but definitive.
- *The Peacock's Tail* — the iridescent display of multiple colours in rapid
  succession that appears in the sealed vessel before the Albedo. This is the
  most common and most reliably reported sign of the Secret Fire operating.
- *Autonomous crystallisation changes* — the crystals in the preparation
  changing form or size without the preparation being disturbed.

*Why it cannot be produced by technique alone.* The Secret Fire arises when
the correct proportion of the three principles — not too much Mercury
volatilising away, not too much Salt crystallising prematurely — has been
established in the sealed vessel and the vessel is maintained at the correct
gentle temperature. The practitioner creates the conditions; the mineral itself
produces the Secret Fire. This is the literal meaning of "Art assists Nature"
in the mineral kingdom.

The practitioner who has developed the inner Secret Fire through two and a
half years of practice — who has sustained the inner flame through meditation,
through vigil, through the dark periods of the Nigredo — will recognise the
mineral's Secret Fire as a reflection of the same universal principle at a
different vibratory level. This recognition is not mysticism; it is the
perceptual attunement that two years of systematic practice have built.

=== Topics This Week

- The Secret Fire as a specific, recognisable phenomenon
- Signs: autonomous colour change, self-generated warmth, Peacock's Tail,
  crystallisation changes
- Why conditions must be established before the Fire arises — it is never forced
- The inner Secret Fire as the practitioner's preparation for recognising the mineral's

#inner-work[
  *The Inner and Outer Fire — Year Three Reading*

  Revisit the Inner Flame practice from Year One Month 3, now with two and a
  half years of accumulated practice behind it.

  Sit for thirty minutes. Attend to the inner flame. How has its quality changed
  since Year One? Is it more stable? More subtle? More present in the body rather
  than requiring deliberate visualisation? Record the comparison honestly.

  This is the Secret Fire of the practitioner. The mineral's Secret Fire is the
  same principle at the mineral vibratory level.
]

